==Walkthrough==
===Sneaking back===
'''''Items required:''''' [[Gas mask]]
{{Checklist|
*To begin speak to [[Elena]] in [[East Ardougne]] (directly west of [[shortcut]] log). {{Chat option|1I'll try to retrieve it for you.}}
*Speak to [[Jerico]] in the house just south of the northern [[Ardougne]] [[bank]] (The house with pigeons cages in the backyard).
*Search the cupboard to obtain [[bird feed]] (click continue or the bird feed won't be added to your inventory).
*Grab a [[pigeon cage]] from the backyard (note: if you are planning on doing [[One Small Favour]], grab an extra 5 pigeon cages).
*Go west to the small watchtower along the wall, in front of the gates to [[West Ardougne]].
*Stand in the corner where the two spiked fences meet.
*Use [[bird feed]] on the watchtower fence.
*Click ''open'' on the [[pigeon cage]] in your inventory.
*Equip your [[gas mask]].
*Run south from the watchtower and speak to [[Omart]]. {{Chat option|1Ok, lets do it.}} After a slight delay, you will arrive in West Ardougne.
}}

===Infiltrating the Mourner Headquarters===
'''''Items required:''' None '''Recommended: '''[[Skills necklace(6)]] (teleport to [[Fishing Guild]]) OR Ardougne teleport to quickly return to [[Elena]].''[[File:Biohazard - Mourner Tunnels.png|thumb|200px|Mourner HQ is due north-east of West Ardougne.]]
{{Checklist|
*Head around the [[Mourner Headquarters|headquarters]] to the northeastern area with the vat and mangle.
*Squeeze through the fence into the backyard.
*Pick up the [[rotten apple]].
*Use the [[rotten apple]] on the cauldron.
*Go back through the fence.
}}
[[File:Nurse Sarah location.png|thumb|120px|Nurse Sarah's house.]]
{{Checklist|
*Go to [[Nurse Sarah]]'s house, south-west of the West Ardougne church.
*Search cupboard in northern part of the house for a [[medical gown]].
*Equip the [[medical gown]], go back to the headquarters and open the door.
*Go upstairs and kill a [[mourner]]. A [[Key (Biohazard)|key]] will automatically be placed in your inventory.
*Use the key on the gate to get into the caged room.
*Search the crates to find [[Elena]]'s [[distillator]] (north-eastern [middle] single crate).
*With 3 empty inventory spaces, return to Elena  and give her the distillator (via [[Ardougne Teleport]], [[Skills necklace]] teleport to the [[Fishing Guild]], over the wall by [[Kilron]], or via the sewers from the [[Plague City]] quest).
}}

===Getting the touch paper===
'''''Items required:''' None '''Recommended:''' 30 coins or a teleport to Rimmington such as House Teleport or Skills necklace to Crafting Guild.'' 
[[File:Chemist location.png|thumb|200px|The chemist's location.]]
{{Checklist|
*Go to the [[Chemist]] in south-western [[Rimmington]] (you can take a ship from [[Captain Barnaby]] at the Ardougne Dock directly to Rimmington for 30gp or use a teleport as the vials won't break upon teleportation anymore)
*Speak to the [[Chemist]] {{Chat option|2Your quest.}}

}}
''He will give you the [[touch paper]].''

===Foresight===
'''''Items required:''' [[Liquid honey]], [[ethenea]], [[sulphuric broline]], and the [[plague sample]].''
{{Checklist|
*You will find [[Chancy]], [[Da Vinci]] and [[Hops (Biohazard)|Hops]] around a fire outside the [[Chemist]]'s house.
*Give Chancy the {{plink|Liquid honey}}. {{Chat option|2You give him the vial of liquid honey...}}
*Give Da Vinci the {{plink|Ethenea}}. {{Chat option|1You give him the vial of ethenea...}}
*Give Hops the {{plink|Sulphuric broline}}. {{Chat option|3You give him the vial of sulphuric broline...}}
**'''If you happen to give the wrong item to one of the henchmen you must then give the rest of them an item and talk to each one of them in Varrock before being able to give them the correct items again.'''
}}
===So far, so good===
'''''Items required:''' 12 [[coins]] or a [[priest gown]] top and bottom, the [[plague sample]] and [[touch paper]].''
{{Checklist|
*Teleport to [[Varrock]]
*Travel to the fenced area to the south-east of the bank (south-eastern Varrock). The guard will search you, but you will be able to pass freely with the plague sample and touch paper in your inventory.
*(Optional) Speak to the Asyff, the [[Fancy dress shop owner]], to get a free [[priest gown]] (top and bottom). Alternatively, purchase a [[priest gown]] (top and bottom) from the [[Fancy dress shop owner]] in the building southeast, and equip it.
*Go to the [[Dancing Donkey Inn]].
*Talk to [[Hops (Biohazard)|Hops]], [[Da Vinci]] and [[Chancy]] to get the vials back. '''Make sure you have the free inventory space.'''
**'''{{Colour|red|Do not}} pass back through the gate or your vials will be confiscated by the guard and you will have to get new samples from Elena again and continue the quest from that point.'''
**'''If you must pass through the gate to retrieve the plague sample or papers, you can drop the vials at the gate, quickly run to Varrock east bank for the items, and run back to pick up the vials.'''
}}

===Secrets===
'''''Items required:''' The [[plague sample]], [[touch paper]], a [[priest gown]], and an [[Ardougne teleport]] (51+ [[Magic]] suggested).''
{{Checklist|
*With your [[Priest gown]] equipped head to [[Guidor]]'s house in the south-east of the fenced area.
*Speak to [[Guidor]], tell him [[Elena]] has sent a sample that needs to be processed. {{Chat option|1I've come to ask your assistance in stopping a plague.}}
*Return to [[Ardougne]] and speak to [[Elena]].
*Go to the {{FloorNumber|uk=1}} of [[Ardougne Castle]] and speak to [[King Lathas]]. {{Chat option|1I don't understand...}}
}}

'''Congratulations! Quest complete!'''

